result.execSummary:
The defendant Emmanuell M Dotson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Emmanuell M Dotson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Emmanuell M Dotson was found guilty of Repeated Sexual Assault of Same Child (At Least 3 Violations of 1st or 2nd Degree Sexual Assault), a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.025(1)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Length of confinement and length of extended supervision for a total length of 40 years bifurcated sentence.

superMiscConds.notes: Defendant must submit a DNA sample as required by law if not previously provided.  Defendant must pay mandatory DNA surcharge.  Defendant must pay all outstanding fees and court obligations.  If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.
Alcohol assessment and follow through with recommendations. No alcohol, random UA's at discretion of agent.

Drug assessment and follow through with recommendations. No controlled substances, random UA's at discretion of agent.  Do not associate with any known drug dealers or users.  Defendant may only take medication pursuant to a prescription.

No contact with the victim or children of the victim (person, property, residence or family).  No contact with minors without agent approval or parental approval.  Defendant must register with the Sex Offender Registry and comply with all rules and requirements of the Sex Offender Registry.  Sex Offender Treatment.  No computer, internet, modem, or smartphone possession or usage without agent's approval.  Counseling, treatment, services as deemed appropriate by agent. Defendant must obey all rules and regulations of probation.   Firearm warning given.  Ineligible voting notice and acknowledgement.
